sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / Platform Ingress
    participant Server as NeMo Guardrails Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant InputRails as Input Rails Pipeline
    participant Embeddings as Embedding Provider<br/>(FastEmbed/OpenAI/NIM)
    participant LLM as Upstream LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OutputRails as Output Rails Pipeline
    participant ContentSafety as Content Safety Model<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,ContentSafety: Flow 1: Chat Completion with Guardrails (LLMRails)

    Client->>Server: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Authorization: Bearer Token
    Server->>Server: Select engine (LLMRails or IORails)<br/>based on config
    Server->>InputRails: Execute input rails pipeline
    InputRails->>Embeddings: Generate embeddings for<br/>similarity-based checks
    Embeddings-->>InputRails: Embedding vectors
    InputRails->>LLM: Evaluate content safety<br/>Bearer Token / API key
    LLM-->>InputRails: Safety evaluation result

    alt Input BLOCKED
        InputRails-->>Server: BLOCKED (rail violation)
        Server-->>Client: 200 OK (blocked response message)
    else Input PASSED
        InputRails-->>Server: PASSED
        Server->>LLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Bearer Token (forwarded from client or env var)
        LLM-->>Server: LLM response
        Server->>OutputRails: Execute output rails pipeline
        OutputRails->>LLM: Evaluate output safety
        LLM-->>OutputRails: Safety evaluation result

        alt Output BLOCKED
            OutputRails-->>Server: BLOCKED
            Server-->>Client: 200 OK (blocked response message)
        else Output PASSED
            OutputRails-->>Server: PASSED (or MODIFIED)
            Server-->>Client: 200 OK (LLM response)
        end
    end

    Note over Client,ContentSafety: Flow 2: Guardrail Check Only (No LLM Generation)

    Client->>Server: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>Authorization: Bearer Token
    Server->>Server: Route to input/output/tool_input<br/>rails based on message role
    Server->>ContentSafety: Evaluate against configured rails<br/>Bearer Token / API key
    ContentSafety-->>Server: Rail evaluation result
    Server-->>Client: RailsResult {status: PASSED/MODIFIED/BLOCKED}

    Note over Client,ContentSafety: Flow 3: Embedding-based Guardrail Evaluation

    Server->>Embeddings: Compute embeddings<br/>(local FastEmbed or API call)
    Embeddings-->>Server: Embedding vectors
    Server->>Server: Annoy ANN index lookup<br/>(local file I/O)
    Server->>LLM: Similarity-based rail evaluation<br/>HTTPS/443 Bearer Token
    LLM-->>Server: Evaluation result
